Tracie Eaton is an-award winning contemporary artist, specializing in acrylic-and mixed media a original paintings. Her artistic career spans over 16 years. She lived on the Gold Coast , Australia 

The high demand for Tracie’s work has lead to a waitlist for commissioned artworks, along with sold out exhibitions and events.

Tracie is trained in Occupational Therapy and Colour Psychology, with her artistic style reflective of her passionate belief in the emotional impact colour has on us all. 

Tracie has won, and continuous to win awards worldwide for her excellence in artistic flair, merit, creative style and contributions to society. She regularly featured in international art publications as one of the most investable global contemporary artists of this time.

Tracie is recognized for her originality. She is an inspiration to all who meet her, described by a client at her Gallery Opening in 2001 as “Tracie is infectious. Sprinkling her joyousness around freely.

collections.name: GirlZ of Z future
collections.description: Eric has made a remarkable mark in the art world, achieving four significant photo exhibitions in Paris. His first exhibition, titled "Destiny", captivated audiences at Manray, while "Girlz of Z Future" was showcased in the prestigious restaurant Saut du Loup at the Louvre, a true honor for any artist. Additionally, his work "L'Éternel Féminin" was displayed within the iconic Alexandre III bridge, a stunning setting that complemented his artistry. This exhibition received the sponsorship and curation of the renowned auctioneer Pierre Cornette de Saint-Cyr, highlighting Eric's growing influence in the art community. Alongside the atmospheric backdrop of Paris, Eric's unique perspective resonates through his powerful imagery, echoing themes that invite conversation and provoke thought, like the evocative "Virgin Suicide" expo.

collections.name: Tardigrades AI BONG
collections.description: The tardigrade bong is a masterpiece of glassblowing, a testament to the artist's skill and imagination. The bong is crafted in the shape of a tardigrade, a microscopic water bear known for its resilience and ability to survive in extreme conditions. The bong's body is segmented, with eight legs and claws, just like the real tardigrade. The glass is clear and thick, with visible ripples and swirls that add to the bong's organic beauty. The bong's water chamber and downstem are seamlessly integrated into the tardigrade's body, creating a functional and aesthetically pleasing design. The bong is a work of art that is both beautiful and functional.
